As f is an embedding, the map \mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  a_0 = a_1 \to  fa_0 = fa_1 has an inverse 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1},\epsilon ,\eta ,\chi \right \rparen \mathclose {}
.

Suppose we have two centres of contraction a,a':A with \chi _\bullet \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}a = x and \chi '_\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}a'=x as witnesses of contraction. To identify 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a,\chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
 with 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a',\chi '_\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
, we employ the covariant sum of each of the pointwise path object structures on \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}-=x over the intrinsic path object structure on A, constructing an identification p\colon  a = a' followed by a homotopy H \colon    \mathopen {}\left \lparen   \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {} _*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}  \sim  \chi '_\bullet . Fixing z\colon  A, we compute:
